EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to collective bargaining; removing the exemption
from compliance with any provision of existing law
requiring a meeting to be open or public for certain
proceedings concerning collective bargaining between
public employers and public employees; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law exempts from any provision of existing law which requires a
2 meeting to be open or public certain proceedings conducted relating to collective
3 bargaining between public employers and public employees. Proceedings subject to
4 the exemption include, among others: (1) any negotiation or informal discussion
5 between a local government employer and an employee organization or employees
6 as individuals or between the Executive Department of State Government and a
7 labor organization or employees as individuals; (2) any meeting of a mediator with
8 either party or both parties to a negotiation; and (3) any meeting or investigation
9 conducted by a fact finder or arbitrator. (NRS 288.220, 288.590) Sections 1 and 2
10 of this bill remove the exemption for those specified proceedings.
